# edream_frontend Project Rules

## 🎯 Project Overview

This is a **Next.js 14** project using **TypeScript**, **Tailwind CSS**, and **Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)** architecture pattern. The project includes both admin web pages (`/adminWeb/*`) and user web pages (`/userWeb/*`).

**Tech Stack:**

- Framework: Next.js 14 (App Router)
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Build: Static Export (`output: 'export'`)
- Architecture: Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)

---

## 🏗️ Architecture Pattern: Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)

### Directory Structure

```
src/
├── app/              # Next.js App Router (routing layer)
│   ├── adminWeb/     # Admin web pages
│   └── userWeb/      # User web pages
├── entities/         # Business entities (reusable domain logic)
├── features/         # Feature units (business features)
├── widgets/          # Composite UI components
└── shared/           # Shared resources
    ├── config/       # Configuration
    ├── hooks/        # Custom hooks
    ├── lib/          # Utilities
    ├── styles/       # Styles
    └── ui/           # Common UI components
```

### Layer Responsibilities

1. **app/**: Next.js page routing only

   - `page.tsx`: Page components
   - `layout.tsx`: Layout wrappers
   - **CRITICAL**: Must contain ONLY routing logic, NO UI markup

2. **entities/**: Domain entities

   - `api/`: Entity-specific API services
   - `model/`: Business logic/state management
   - `ui/`: Entity-related UI components

3. **features/**: Feature units

   - Structure: `{featureName}/{action}/`
   - Example: `adminWeb/member/list/`
   - Contains: `api/`, `model/`, `ui/`

4. **widgets/**: Composite components

   - Examples: `AdminLayout`, `Header`, `Sidebar`

5. **shared/**: Shared resources
   - Reusable utilities, hooks, UI, styles

### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Dependency Rules

**MUST follow this dependency flow:**

```
app → widgets → features → entities → shared
```

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Import from upper layers (e.g., `features` importing from `widgets`)
- ❌ Create circular dependencies
- ❌ Import directly from `app/` in `features/` or `entities/`
- ❌ Mix concerns between layers

**MUST:**

- ✅ Only import from same layer or lower layers
- ✅ Use absolute paths with `@/` prefix
- ✅ Re-export through `index.ts` files

### ⚠️ CRITICAL: App Layer Purity Rule

**MUST ALWAYS verify `app/` layer contains ONLY routing logic when:**

- ✅ Creating new pages in `app/` directory
- ✅ Refactoring existing pages to FSD structure
- ✅ Copying code patterns from existing pages
- ✅ Migrating legacy code to FSD architecture

**MUST ensure `app/` pages contain ONLY:**

- ✅ Layout wrapper (`<AdminLayout>`)
- ✅ Feature/widget component import and rendering
- ✅ Route parameter handling (query params, path params)
- ✅ Suspense boundaries for async operations

**MUST NOT include in `app/` layer:**

- ❌ **NEVER** include UI markup (page headers, breadcrumbs, cards, containers)
- ❌ **NEVER** include form elements, buttons, inputs
- ❌ **NEVER** include styling classes or inline styles
- ❌ **NEVER** include business logic or state management
- ❌ **NEVER** include API calls or data fetching
- ❌ **NEVER** copy UI markup from existing pages without verification

**Why this is CRITICAL:**

The `app/` layer is Next.js's routing layer. Violating this rule breaks FSD architecture and creates:

1. ❌ Mixing concerns between routing and presentation
2. ❌ Duplicate UI code across pages
3. ❌ Harder maintenance and refactoring
4. ❌ Violation of single responsibility principle

**Real-world example of the mistake:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG: UI markup in app/ layer
// src/app/adminWeb/member/register/page.tsx
export default function MemberRegisterPage() {
  return (
    <AdminLayout>
      <div className="page-header">
        {" "}
        {/* ❌ UI markup */}
        <h1 className="page-title">관리자회원등록</h1>
        <nav className="breadcrumb">
          {" "}
          {/* ❌ UI markup */}
          <span>홈</span> &gt; <span>관리자</span>
        </nav>
      </div>
      <div className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow">
        {" "}
        {/* ❌ UI markup */}
        <div className="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h5 className="text-lg font-semibold mb-0">회원 정보 입력</h5>
        </div>
        <div className="p-0">
          <MemberRegisterForm />
        </div>
      </div>
    </AdminLayout>
  );
}
```

**Correct FSD-compliant pattern:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Only routing in app/ layer
// src/app/adminWeb/member/register/page.tsx
export default function MemberRegisterPage() {
  return (
    <AdminLayout>
      <MemberRegisterPageView />{" "}
      {/* ✅ Feature/widget component handles all UI */}
    </AdminLayout>
  );
}

// ✅ CORRECT: UI markup in features/ui/ or widgets/
// src/features/adminWeb/member/register/ui/MemberRegisterPageView.tsx
export const MemberRegisterPageView: React.FC = () => {
  return (
    <>
      <div className="page-header">
        <h1 className="page-title">관리자회원등록</h1>
        <nav className="breadcrumb">
          <span>홈</span> &gt; <span>관리자</span>
        </nav>
      </div>
      <div className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow">
        <div className="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h5 className="text-lg font-semibold mb-0">회원 정보 입력</h5>
        </div>
        <div className="p-0">
          <MemberRegisterForm />
        </div>
      </div>
    </>
  );
};
```

**Reference pattern (CORRECT example in codebase):**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: src/app/adminWeb/login/page.tsx (reference implementation)
"use client";

import { LoginForm } from "@/features/adminWeb/auth/login/ui";

export default function LoginPage() {
  return <LoginForm />; // ✅ Only routing, no UI markup
}
```

**Prevention Checklist (MUST verify before creating/modifying app/ pages):**

- [ ] `app/` page contains ONLY `<AdminLayout>` wrapper and component import
- [ ] NO `<div>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`, or other HTML elements with classes
- [ ] NO Tailwind classes in `app/` layer files
- [ ] NO inline styles in `app/` layer files
- [ ] All UI markup is in `features/ui/` or `widgets/` layers
- [ ] Reference `src/app/adminWeb/login/page.tsx` as the correct pattern
- [ ] Verify existing code before copying patterns (some may violate FSD)

**When refactoring existing pages:**

1. **First step**: Identify all UI markup in `app/` layer
2. **Second step**: Extract UI markup to `features/ui/{featureName}PageView.tsx` or `widgets/`
3. **Third step**: Update `app/` page to import and render only the extracted component
4. **Fourth step**: Verify no UI markup remains in `app/` layer

**Common patterns to avoid:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG: Don't do this
<div className="page-header">...</div>
<div className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow">...</div>
<nav className="breadcrumb">...</nav>

// ✅ CORRECT: Do this instead
<PageViewComponent />  // Component in features/ui/ or widgets/
```

**Decision tree for page structure:**

```
Creating new page?
├─ Does it need routing only?
│  └─ YES → Put in app/ (NO UI markup)
└─ Does it need UI structure?
   └─ YES → Create in features/ui/ or widgets/
      └─ Import and render from app/
```

