## 🏗️ Build / Typecheck Guardrails (MUST READ)

This project uses **Next.js 14 + TypeScript + Static Export (`output: 'export'`)**.
Because of that, **`npm run build` performs stricter checks** than `npm run dev`:

- It runs **full typechecking** across the project
- It **generates static pages for all routes** (so pages you never opened in dev can fail the build)

### ✅ MUST: Always verify build before merging

- **MUST**: Run `npm run build` before merge/release (type errors must be 0)
- **MUST**: Fix TypeScript errors at the source (do not hide with `any` / `ts-ignore`)

### ✅ MUST: API params must match the typed request interface

- **MUST**: When calling services like `XxxService.getXxxList(params)`, `params` MUST satisfy the request type (e.g., `ProgramListParams`)
- **MUST**: If the request type requires server-side pagination fields (commonly `length`, `start`), they MUST be provided
- **MUST NOT**: Pass partial objects that “work in dev” but violate the type (build will fail)

### ✅ MUST: Form errors type must include every UI-referenced field

- **MUST**: If UI references `errors.someField`, then the errors type/interface MUST include `someField?: string`
- **MUST NOT**: Reference `errors.xxx` in UI unless it exists in the errors type

### ✅ MUST: Lucide icon props (build-only type failures)

Lucide React icons often **do not accept `title` prop** (TypeScript build fails).

- **MUST NOT**: `<SomeLucideIcon title="..."/>`
- **MUST**: Use one of:
  - `aria-label="..."` on the icon
  - Wrap the icon: `<span title="..."><Icon ... /></span>`

### Component Types

**MUST:**

```typescript
// Option 1: React.FC
export const Header: React.FC<HeaderProps> = ({ onToggleSidebar }) => {
  // ...
};

// Option 2: Explicit function
export function LoginForm() {
  // ...
}

// Option 3: Arrow function with explicit return type
export const AdminLayout: React.FC<AdminLayoutProps> = ({ children }) => {
  // ...
};
```

**MUST NOT:**

```typescript
// ❌ Missing type annotation
export const Header = ({ onToggleSidebar }) => {};

// ❌ Using any
export const Component: React.FC<any> = (props) => {};
```

