## 📦 Import Rules

### Import Order (MUST follow this exact order)

**MUST:**

```typescript
// 1. React and Next.js imports
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import { useRouter } from "next/navigation";

// 2. Third-party libraries
import { someLibrary } from "some-library";

// 3. Internal modules (absolute paths with @/)
import { AuthService } from "@/entities/auth/api";
import { AdminLayout } from "@/widgets/admin/layout";
import { useMemberList } from "@/features/adminWeb/member/list/model";

// 4. Relative imports (only if necessary)
import { LocalComponent } from "./LocalComponent";

// 5. Styles (always last)
// Note: Custom CSS imports are specific to admin pages (see admin-web-rules.mdc)
// User pages use Tailwind CSS only (see user-web-rules.mdc)
```

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Mix import orders
- ❌ Use relative paths when absolute paths are available
- ❌ Import styles before code imports
- ❌ Use wildcard imports (`import * as`)

### Import Path Rules

**MUST:**

- ✅ Use `@/` prefix for all internal imports
- ✅ Import from `index.ts` when available
- ✅ Group imports by category (React, libraries, internal, styles)

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Use relative paths like `../../../` (use `@/` instead)
- ❌ Import from implementation files when `index.ts` exists

