## 🎨 Styling Rules

### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Tailwind CSS Configuration

**MUST ALWAYS verify `tailwind.config.js` content paths when:**

- ✅ Creating new FSD layers (app, entities, features, widgets, shared)
- ✅ Moving files between FSD layers
- ✅ Restructuring project directories
- ✅ Adding new component directories
- ✅ Converting from non-FSD to FSD architecture

**MUST ensure ALL FSD layers are included in `content` array:**

```javascript
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  content: [
    "./src/pages/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}",
    "./src/app/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}", // ✅ App Router pages
    "./src/shared/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}", // ✅ Shared resources
    "./src/entities/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}", // ✅ Business entities
    "./src/widgets/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}", // ✅ Composite components
    "./src/features/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}", // ✅ Feature units (CRITICAL!)
  ],
  // ...
};
```

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ **NEVER** forget to add `features` path when using FSD architecture
- ❌ **NEVER** assume Tailwind will auto-detect new directories
- ❌ **NEVER** skip updating `tailwind.config.js` after directory restructuring
- ❌ **NEVER** ignore missing CSS without checking Tailwind config first

**Why this is CRITICAL:**

Tailwind CSS uses **purge/content scanning** to generate CSS. It ONLY scans files in the `content` array. If a directory is missing:

1. ❌ Tailwind classes in that directory won't be detected
2. ❌ CSS won't be generated for those classes
3. ❌ Styles will appear broken/missing in the browser
4. ❌ No build errors will occur (silent failure)

**Real-world example of the mistake:**

```javascript
// ❌ WRONG: Missing 'features' path
content: [
  "./src/app/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}",
  "./src/shared/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}",
  "./src/entities/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}",
  "./src/widgets/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}",
  // ❌ Missing: './src/features/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}'
];

// Result: LoginForm.tsx in features/adminWeb/auth/login/ui/
// uses classes like 'bg-gradient-to-r', 'from-blue-500', 'to-indigo-500'
// but these classes are NOT in the generated CSS because the file wasn't scanned!
```

**Prevention Checklist (MUST verify before considering CSS issues resolved):**

- [ ] All FSD layers (app, entities, features, widgets, shared) are in `content` array
- [ ] Path patterns match actual directory structure
- [ ] File extensions match project file types (`.tsx`, `.ts`, `.jsx`, `.js`, `.mdx`)
- [ ] After adding new directories, `tailwind.config.js` is updated
- [ ] After restructuring, `tailwind.config.js` is verified
- [ ] Build cache is cleared after config changes (`.next` folder)

**Debugging missing CSS:**

1. **First check**: Verify `tailwind.config.js` content paths include the file's directory
2. **Second check**: Clear build cache (`.next` folder) and restart dev server
3. **Third check**: Verify Tailwind classes are actually used in the component
4. **Fourth check**: Check browser DevTools to see if CSS classes exist in generated stylesheet

### Tailwind CSS Usage

**MUST:**

- ✅ Use Tailwind utility classes as primary styling method
- ✅ Use responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`
- ✅ Use custom colors from `tailwind.config.js`
- ✅ Follow mobile-first approach

**Example:**

```tsx
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700">
  Button
</button>

<div className="w-full md:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3">
  <span className="text-[13px] sm:text-[11px] md:text-[13px]">
